since X/Y series, where we where given Sylveon; species evolved from purity/love. So it's speculation right now that we just may get a new Eeveelution, it's possible. Though I can say right about now, producer's are finally showing Eevee's full potential and really well too.

Currently Eevee hasn't tried to evolve, to test that theory. But it's capable of using moves and skill's that it's evolved form's can do. Unusual? Not unusual at all, as this is a highly adaptable species of Pokémon, and a much loved champion. We haven't had a eeveelution

Now let's go into Chloe's Eevee!
So far it's indecisive on what to evolve into, and wisely. As once it's chosen to evolve, it'll be permanent, right? This Eevee has had tests done on it, maybe not to the extent of what Vee went through.
Of course it is and would have been possible, with the high amounts of say - ice, dark or grass energy, that Vee could have also taken to using other eeveelution form's.

Vee was what this Eevee was called. And it's reason for having reached the potential of being able to evolve into these forms, was because of the mutation it went through, because of the element needed. Fire, Water and Electric. https://t.co/B1KPEZQqby

Okay so I've realized something about Eevee, and will admit that the series never really did go into detail about how unstable it's genetics can be. Going back into earlier Gen with the Eevee that could evolve into different forms then return to it's normal state.
